Katherine Archuleta has been confirmed as the next Director of the Office of Personnel Management by the Senate. The President commends this decision, stating that Archuleta has a strong background and dedication to recruiting and retaining a high-quality workforce. She is known for advocating for public service and federal workers and shares President Obama's vision for diversity and inclusion in the federal workforce. Archuleta is expected to be a champion for federal workers and their commitment to public service.